tutorial
install json
install bash
open bash terminal and type:
npm i -g yo generator-code
yo code
select new color theme with the arrow keys
answer the questions
after that, you have to type on bash:
code ./'your theme identifier here' - mine is: "pupim-s-theme"
so I typed : code ./pupim-s-theme
It will open another vscode tab
Open "themes" and you themethere you can edit whatever you want.
To see your theme, just hit F5
After the theme is done and package.json is already configured, run in bash:
1) npm i -g vsce
2) vsce package
created a file .vsix and this is the theme ready to install it locally
to install your file, type in bash:
code --install-extension "theme-name-here.vsix"